<blockquote>
<p><strong>Global paid search spending will reach $218.3 billion in 2026.</strong> The average Google Ads CPC is $5.26. CPC increased for 87% of industries in 2025. The average PPC ROI is $2 for every $1 spent.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>PPC statistics shape budget decisions, bidding strategies, and channel allocation for every marketing team running paid ads. The numbers change fast. What worked last year costs more this year.</p>
<p>We compiled 38 PPC statistics from WordStream, Google, Shopify, and other primary sources. Every stat includes the source and year.</p>
<p>Here is what the data covers:</p>
<ul>
<li>Global PPC market size and spending trends</li>
<li>Average CPC and conversion rates by industry</li>
<li>Google Ads performance benchmarks</li>
<li>PPC ROI and cost per lead data</li>
<li><a href="/blog/seo-vs-ppc/">PPC vs SEO</a> performance comparisons</li>
<li>Mobile and platform-specific advertising data</li>
</ul>
<p><img loading="lazy" alt="PPC statistics for 2026 showing key cost and performance benchmarks" src="/images/blog/ppc-statistics-2026-overview.webp" /></p>
<h2>PPC Market Size and Spending Statistics</h2>
<p><strong>1. Global search advertising spend will reach $218.3 billion in 2026.</strong>
(Source: <a href="https://www.statista.com/outlook/dmo/digital-advertising/search-advertising/worldwide">Statista</a>, 2026)
That is up from $212 billion in 2025, an increase of roughly 3%. The market is projected to surpass $247 billion by 2028.</p>
<p><strong>2. The United States accounts for $156.34 billion in search ad spend.</strong>
(Source: Statista, 2025)
The US generates over 70% of global search advertising revenue. No other country comes close.</p>
<p><strong>3. Google Ads holds 39.2% of global digital ad market share.</strong>
(Source: <a href="https://www.demandsage.com/google-ads-statistics/">DemandSage</a>, 2025)
Meta platforms (Facebook + Instagram) hold 18.7%. Amazon Ads captures 11.3%. Microsoft Advertising holds 3.8%.</p>
<p><strong>4. 65% of small to mid-sized businesses run at least one PPC campaign.</strong>
(Source: <a href="https://www.designrush.com/agency/paid-media-pay-per-click/trends/ppc-statistics">DesignRush</a>, 2025)
PPC adoption among SMBs continues to grow. However, 35% of small businesses still do not use paid search at all.</p>
<p><strong>5. The PPC software market grew to $22.49 billion in 2025.</strong>
(Source: <a href="https://ecommercebonsai.com/ppc-statistics/">Ecommerce Bonsai</a>, 2025)
That figure covers bid management tools, analytics platforms, and automation software. The market is growing at 9.8% CAGR.</p>
<p><strong>6. 93% of marketers rate PPC as effective or highly effective.</strong>
(Source: <a href="https://www.shopify.com/blog/ppc-statistics">Shopify</a>, 2026)
Despite rising costs, marketer confidence in PPC remains high. The immediate visibility and measurable results drive continued investment.</p>
<h2>Google Ads Cost Per Click Statistics</h2>
<p><img loading="lazy" alt="Average CPC by industry for Google Ads in 2026" src="/images/blog/ppc-cpc-by-industry-2026.webp" /></p>
<p><strong>7. The average Google Ads CPC is $5.26.</strong>
(Source: <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/2025-google-ads-benchmarks">WordStream</a>, 2025)
This represents the average across all industries for search campaigns. The figure has increased significantly from $2.69 in previous years.</p>
<p><strong>8. CPC increased for 87% of industries in 2025.</strong>
(Source: WordStream, 2025)
Only 13% of industries saw stable or declining CPCs. Rising competition and AI-driven bidding are pushing costs higher across the board.</p>
<p><strong>9. Attorneys and legal services have the highest CPC at $8.58.</strong>
(Source: WordStream, 2025)
Legal keywords are the most expensive in Google Ads. A single click on "personal injury lawyer" can cost $50+.</p>
<p><strong>10. Dentists and home improvement tie for second at $7.85 CPC.</strong>
(Source: WordStream, 2025)
Service-based local businesses face steep CPCs because each click represents a high-value customer.</p>
<p><strong>11. Arts and entertainment has the lowest CPC at $1.60.</strong>
(Source: WordStream, 2025)
Low-CPC industries typically have lower customer lifetime values or less competition for search terms.</p>
<p><strong>12. Google Shopping Ads average $0.66 CPC.</strong>
(Source: <a href="https://www.storegrowers.com/google-ads-benchmarks/">Store Growers</a>, 2025)
Shopping campaigns cost a fraction of search campaigns. For ecommerce, Shopping Ads deliver the best cost efficiency.</p>
<p><strong>13. Display ad CPC averages $0.63.</strong>
(Source: Store Growers, 2025)
Display campaigns are cheap per click but convert at much lower rates than search. They serve awareness, not direct response.</p>
<p><strong>14. Beauty and personal care CPC increased 40% year over year.</strong>
(Source: WordStream, 2025)
The sharpest CPC increase of any industry. D2C brands entering Google Ads are driving prices up in beauty verticals.</p>
