<h2>Platform Market Share Statistics</h2>
<p><strong>26. Google controls 90.5% of the global search engine market.</strong>
(Source: <a href="https://www.demandsage.com/google-ads-statistics/">DemandSage</a>, 2025)
Bing holds 3.4%. Yahoo holds 1.2%. For paid search, Google Ads is effectively the only platform that matters at scale.</p>
<p><strong>27. Meta Ads (Facebook + Instagram) capture 18.7% of digital ad spend.</strong>
(Source: DemandSage, 2025)
Meta is the second-largest advertising platform. But Meta Ads target social feeds, not search intent. The use case differs from PPC.</p>
<p><strong>28. Amazon Ads grew to 11.3% of digital ad market share.</strong>
(Source: DemandSage, 2025)
Amazon PPC is growing faster than any other platform. For ecommerce brands, Amazon Ads often outperform Google Shopping on ROI.</p>
<p><strong>29. Microsoft Advertising (Bing Ads) holds 3.8% market share.</strong>
(Source: DemandSage, 2025)
Bing Ads typically have 20-30% lower CPCs than Google. For budget-constrained advertisers, Bing offers a less competitive auction.</p>
<h2>Mobile and Device Statistics</h2>
<p><strong>30. Mobile devices account for 52% of all PPC clicks.</strong>
(Source: <a href="https://www.shopify.com/blog/ppc-statistics">Shopify</a>, 2026)
Mobile PPC traffic now exceeds desktop. But mobile conversion rates lag behind desktop by 30-50%.</p>
<p><strong>31. Mobile CPC averages 24% less than desktop CPC.</strong>
(Source: Promodo, 2025)
Lower mobile CPCs reflect lower conversion rates. Advertisers bid less because mobile clicks are less likely to convert.</p>
<p><strong>32. 60% of smartphone users contact businesses directly from search results.</strong>
(Source: <a href="https://thesocialshepherd.com/blog/google-ads-ppc-statistics">Social Shepherd</a>, 2025)
Click-to-call ads perform well on mobile. Local service businesses see the strongest mobile PPC results.</p>
<p><strong>33. Video ad spending will reach $191.3 billion in 2026.</strong>
(Source: Statista, 2026)
YouTube and short-form video ads are the fastest-growing PPC format. Video CPC is typically lower than search CPC.</p>
<h2>Industry-Specific PPC Benchmarks</h2>
<p><strong>34. The average CPC across all industries for LinkedIn Ads is $5.58.</strong>
(Source: <a href="https://ppcchief.com/blog/average-cpc-by-ad-platform-2026">PPC Chief</a>, 2026)
LinkedIn has the highest CPC of any social platform. B2B advertisers pay premium prices for professional audience targeting.</p>
<p><strong>35. Indeed job ads average $1.21 CPC.</strong>
(Source: PPC Chief, 2026)
Recruitment PPC is significantly cheaper than B2B or legal advertising. High ad volume keeps auction prices low.</p>
<p><strong>36. The average small business Google Ads budget is $1,000-$10,000 per month.</strong>
(Source: <a href="https://www.webfx.com/blog/ppc/much-cost-advertise-google-adwords/">WebFX</a>, 2026)
At $5.26 average CPC, a $5,000 monthly budget yields roughly 950 clicks. At a 4.4% conversion rate, that produces about 42 leads per month.</p>
<p><strong>37. Education and instruction CPC increased over 40% year over year.</strong>
(Source: WordStream, 2025)
The second-sharpest CPC increase after beauty. Online education competition is driving prices up fast.</p>
<p><strong>38. The global PPC market will reach $483.55 billion by 2029.</strong>
(Source: Statista, 2026)
Despite rising costs and organic alternatives, paid search spending continues its upward trajectory.</p>
<h2>Key Takeaways</h2>
<ul>
<li><strong>$218.3B</strong>. Global search ad spend in 2026</li>
<li><strong>$5.26</strong>. Average Google Ads CPC (up for 87% of industries)</li>
<li><strong>4.4%</strong>. Average Google Ads conversion rate</li>
<li><strong>$2 per $1</strong>. Average PPC ROI (vs $7.48 for SEO)</li>
<li><strong>$181</strong>. Average PPC cost per lead (vs $31 for SEO)</li>
<li><strong>52%</strong>. PPC clicks from mobile devices</li>
<li><strong>70-80%</strong>. Users who skip ads and click organic results</li>
</ul>
<h2>Methodology</h2>
<p><strong>Sources:</strong> WordStream, Statista, DemandSage, Shopify, WebFX, First Page Sage, Store Growers, Uproas, Promodo, PPC Chief, Social Shepherd, Marketing Code, SeoProfy, AIOSEO, DesignRush, Ecommerce Bonsai.</p>
<p><strong>Last updated:</strong> March 2026</p>
<p><strong>Note:</strong> We update this page quarterly. Each statistic includes its original source and year. CPC and conversion figures represent averages across campaigns and may vary by geography, bidding strategy, and campaign optimization.</p>
