<h2>FAQ</h2>
<p><strong>What is the average cost per click for Google Ads in 2026?</strong></p>
<p>The average Google Ads CPC is $5.26 across all industries. Legal services has the highest CPC at $8.58. Arts and entertainment has the lowest at $1.60. Google Shopping Ads average $0.66. CPCs increased for 87% of industries in 2025.</p>
<p><strong>Is PPC worth the investment in 2026?</strong></p>
<p>PPC delivers immediate visibility and measurable results. The average ROI is $2 for every $1 spent. However, <a href="/blog/seo-roi-statistics/">SEO delivers $7.48 per $1</a> over time. PPC works best for short-term campaigns, product launches, and testing new markets. For sustained traffic, organic SEO is more cost-effective.</p>
<p><strong>What is a good PPC conversion rate?</strong></p>
<p>The average Google Ads search conversion rate is 4.4%. Automotive (6.8%) and legal services (5.5%) convert highest. A "good" rate depends on your industry, but anything above 5% is strong. Display campaigns average only 1.05%.</p>
<p><strong>How much should a small business spend on PPC?</strong></p>
<p>The average small business Google Ads budget is $1,000-$10,000 per month. At $5.26 average CPC, a $5,000 budget generates about 950 clicks and 42 conversions. Start with $1,000/month, test for 90 days, then scale based on CPA and ROI data.</p>
<p><strong>How does PPC compare to SEO for lead generation?</strong></p>
<p>PPC leads cost $181 on average. SEO leads cost $31. SEO conversion rates average 14.6% vs 3.75% for PPC. PPC delivers faster results (immediate visibility). SEO delivers better long-term ROI. The ideal strategy combines both channels.</p>
<p>PPC costs are rising. Organic clicks are free. Every dollar you invest in SEO content today reduces your dependence on paid ads tomorrow. The businesses investing in both channels now will pay less per customer in 12 months than those relying on PPC alone.</p>
